          <heading>Opinion Announcement of Justice William J. Brennan, Jr.</heading>
          <turn speaker="william_j_brennan_jr" startTime="0.000" stopTime="33.666" flagged="true">
            <label>Justice William J. Brennan, Jr.</label>
            <text syncTime="0.000" offset="">In No. 74-453, a three-judge District Court in the Southern District of New York held that the New York regulation was unconstitutional because in violation of the Due Process Clause.</text>
            <text syncTime="15.221" offset="60813">In light of our decision in 74-5054, we have no occasion to address that or any constitutional question.</text>
            <text syncTime="24.354" offset="97384">Accordingly, we vacate the judgment of the three-judge court and remand with direction to dismiss the case to that extent as moot.</text>
          </turn>
          <turn speaker="warren_e_burger" startTime="33.666" stopTime="88.715" flagged="true">
            <label>Chief Justice Warren E. Burger</label>
            <text syncTime="33.666" offset="134583">Thank you Mr. Justice Brennan.</text>
          </turn>
